{
  "title": "Containerizing Microservices using FastAPI with Python 3.12+",
  "summary": "This explainer will guide you through the process of containerizing microservices using FastAPI, a modern, fast (high-performance), web framework for building APIs with Python 3.12+ and Uvicorn as ASGI server.",
  "key_points": [
    "Understanding Docker and its role in containerization",
    "Setting up development environment: Python 3.12, FastAPI, Uvicorn",
    "Dockerizing the FastAPI application",
    "Building and Running the Docker Container",
    "Exposing the containerized service via Docker Compose",
    "Testing the containerized microservice"
  ],
  "code_examples": [
    {
      "language": "bash",
      "code": "docker build -t fastapi-microservice .\n\ndocker run -p 8000:8000 fastapi-microservice"
    },
    {
      "language": "python",
      "code": "from fastapi import FastAPI\napp = FastAPI()\ndef get_root():\n   return {'Hello, World!'}\napp.get('/', get_root)"
    }
  ],
  "version_notes": [
    "Python 3.12 is required for the examples to run",
    "FastAPI version >= 0.65.x is recommended"
  ],
  "caveats": [
    "Ensure your system has Docker installed before following this guide",
    "This explainer focuses on a single microservice, containerizing multiple services requires additional steps and possibly an orchestration tool like Kubernetes"
  ]
